Office automation: agents write AppleScript (macOS) or PowerShell COM (Windows) scripts, xpressclaw executes them on the host via osascript/powershell. The actual Office app handles formatting — no library-based conversion. Three tools: office_run (custom script), office_read (extract text), office_export (save as PDF). Scripts are auto-wrapped in tell blocks (AppleScript) or COM object creation (PowerShell) if not already present. Skill has full examples for Word/Excel/PowerPoint create and edit.
